<HEAD>Police Go Fishing, Catch Six Vehicles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fishing expedition in the Ohio River netted
city and state police five cars and a late-model truck.
   Acting on a tip, police divers searched the river Thursday and
found the vehicles at the end of a pier near the West End Bridge.
They used a crane to raise them from the river.
   At least 10 more vehicles rest on the bottom of that part of the
river, police said.
   The truck had the name and telephone number of a Pittsburgh
pizzeria on its side. Owner Tim Mohr said the truck was stolen
early Sunday.
