<DOCNO> AP880910-0014 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-10-88 0121EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w BC-TextileBill-Glance     09-10 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Textile Bill-Glance,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With PM-Textile Bill Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here at a glance are provisions of the textile
trade legislation approved Friday by the Senate:
   TEXTILE AND APPAREL IMPORTS
   Freezes overall textile and apparel imports this year at 1987
levels and limits future growth to one percent annually.
   NONRUBBER FOOTWEAR IMPORTS
   Freezes overall imports of nonrubber footwear at 1987 levels
with no provision for increases in the future.
   AGRICULTURAL PROVISION
   Provides for preferred trade treatment for countries that
increase their purchases of U.S. agricultural goods.
   AUCTIONED QUOTAS
   Requires the government to auction off import quotas among
American importing companies.
   COMPENSATION
   Authorizes the president to negotiate reduced tariffs to
compensate countries hurt by tightened import restraints.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
