<HEAD>With PM-Medicaid Abortions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 216-166 roll call Friday by which
the House refused to go along with a Senate amendment expanding
Medicaid abortions to rape and incest victims.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to keep existing law, which limits
Medicaid payments to abortions needed to save a woman's life. A
``no'' vote was to change the law.
   Voting yes were 90 Democrats and 126 Republicans.
   Voting no were 136 Democrats and 30 Republicans.
   X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
