<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Landlsides     09-10 0100</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Landlsides,0102</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Landslides Bury 13</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thirteen people have been buried in
landslides caused by torrential rains in a village west of
Katmandu, officials said.
   The landslides occurred Wednesday in Pangrang village, 112 miles
west of Katmandu.
   Assistant Minister of Works and Transport Chhetra Bahadur Gurung
said Friday that only five bodies had been recovered from the
debris, and rescuers were workin to find the other eight known to
have died, including a pregnant woman.
   Gurung said 30 villagers were injured in the landslides,
including three who were airlifted to nearby Pokhara town for
medical treatment.
</TEXT>
