<2ND_LINE>PM-Britain-Drugs,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thirteen Tons of Marijuana Found on Honduran-Registered Ship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 13-ton stash of marijuana was discovered aboard
a Honduran-registered freighter stopped in British waters last
week, a customs official said.
   ``There's tons of it coming out,'' Peter Biles of the Customs
and Excise Department said Friday of the discovery on the ship,
identified as the Salton Sea. ``It's ... a big pro job.''
   Biles said the ship's Dutch captain, three Dutch crewmen and
four Colombian crewmen were charged with illegally importing
cannabis into Britain and were being held in police custody.
   The Honduran-registered ship was captured Sept. 3 after a chase
across the English Channel from the northeast coast of France,
where it had failed to stop for a routine check by French customs
officers.
   The French fired two warning shots but the freighter churned off
to British waters and finally surrendered to the British coast
guard. It was escorted into Ramsgate on the southeast coast of
England.
