<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0430</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Florence Whips Gulf Coast, Spreads Rain as Far North as New Jersey</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Tropical storm Florence whipped the Gulf Coast with severe winds
today and spread rain as far north as southern New Jersey.
   The storm's strength diminished, and it was downgraded from
hurricane status as it passed by New Orleans and headed for
Mississippi.
   Hurricane warnings had been posted from near Morgan City, La.,
through to Pensacola, Fla., and tropical storm warnings for winds
to 50 mph were posted from Pensacola to Apalachicola, Fla.
   Tides were expected to run as much as 9 feet above normal and
between 5 and 10 inches of rain was likely in areas covered by the
hurricane warning. The Naval Air Station near New Orleans recorded
just under 2{ inches of rain in the six hours ended at 2 a.m. EDT.
   The storm system's northern edge cast rain over Virginia,
Maryland, Delaware and southern New Jersey.
   Most of the rest of the country was dry.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms across
Gulf Coast states from Louisana to the Florida Panhandle and into
Georgia and eastern Tennessee. Widely scattered showers were
expected in central Montana and the mountains of Wyoming.
   Highs were forecast to be in the 60s from the upper Missouri
Valley to the northern Pacific Coast; in the 70s from the rest of
the northern Pacific Coast across the northern Rockies, northern
North Dakota, northern Minnesota, the Great Lakes and northern New
England; in the 90s in the lower and central plains; and near 110
degrees in the desert Southwest; and mostly in the 80s elsewhere.
   At 3 a.m. EDT, temperatures ranged from 37 degrees at Hibbing,
Minn., to 92 degrees at Yuma, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 66 rain; Boston 67 foggy; Buffalo 66 foggy;
Charleston, S.C. 75 foggy; Cincinnati 59 fair; Cleveland 61 foggy;
Detroit 53 fair; Miami 81 fair; New York 71 cloudy; Philadelphia 69
cloudy; Pittsburgh 61 fair; Portland, Maine 62 foggy; Washington 69
foggy.
   _Central: Bismarck 49 cloudy; Chicago 59 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
71 fair; Denver 65 fair; Des Moines 57 partly cloudy; Indianapolis
61 fair; Kansas City 68 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 57 fair;
Nashville 66 partly cloudy; New Orleans 72 showery; St. Louis 65
fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 71 fair; Anchorage 52 cloudy; Las Vegas 83
fair; Los Angeles 62 fair; Phoenix 91 fair; Salt Lake City 76
cloudy; San Diego 68 cloudy; San Francisco 58 cloudy; Seattle 51
fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 61 fair; Toronto 54 fair.
</TEXT>
