<BYLINE>Ignace Dhellemmes</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>YAOUNDE, Cameroon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ignace Dhellemmes, the French
missionary known as the ``father of the pygmies,'' died Wednesday
at age 74.
   Dhellemmes worked from 1948 to 1952 in a leper colony in eastern
Cameroon. He began working among pygmy tribes in 1953.
   In a 1985 autobiography, Dhellemmes described his 40 years of
work in Cameroon and Congo, where he sought to improve the health
and social welfare of pygmy tribes.
