<HEAD>Ethiopian Rebels Say They Sank Three Ships</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eritrean rebels said they sank three ships
and damaged port installations in speedboat attacks along
Ethiopia's Red Sea coast.
   The rebels made the claim Friday in a radio broadcast over the
clandestine Voice of the Broad Masses of Eritrea that was monitored
in Nairobi.
   The Eritrean People's Liberation Front said rebel naval units
carried out the attack Tuesday on the Red Sea port of Massawa, 40
miles northeast of Eritrea's provincial capital Asmara.
   Ethiopia's government in the capital, Addis Ababa, rarely
comments on rebel claims and, there was no way to independently
confirm Friday's report.
   Eritrea, Ethiopia's northernmost province, is home to Africa's
longest civil war, a 27-year-old secessionist struggle. In
neighboring Tigre, rebels have been fighting for 14 years for
greater autonomy for that region.
