<1ST_LINE>r i AM-UN-IranianProtest     09-10 0177</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-UN-Iranian Protest,0183</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iranian Who Set Himself Afire In Protest Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UNITED NATIONS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Iranian man who set himself on fire
during a demonstration against the execution of dissidents in Iran
died Saturday.
   Mehrdad Imen, 32, a registered alien from Los Angeles, died at
New York Hospital-Cornell Medical Center, where he was admitted
Friday.
   Imen set himself ablaze across from the U.N. Headquarters
building about noon Friday as hundreds of Iranians demonstrated in
a nearby park.
   The rally was organized by the People's Mujahedeen, an Iranian
group seeking the overthrow of the government of Ayatollah Ruhollah
Khomeini.
   Imen was well known in the Iranian community as an anti-Khomeini
activist, but was not a member of the People's Mujahedeen, the
group's spokesman, Mohammed Sedaghat, said Saturday in a telephone
interview from Washington.
   Imen flew to New York from Los Angeles on Friday with other
Iraians to join in the demonstration, Sedaghat said.
   ``This was the action of a man who was moved to this extent and
(whose) feelings obviously could not be restrained,'' Sedaghat said.
</TEXT>
