<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--RideHome     09-10 0179</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Ride Home,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police: Theft Suspect Stole Van to go Home From Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A robbery suspect freed without bond walked out of
court and stole a new van for his ride home, police said.
   Mark Bartels told police he took the van ``because he had no way
to get home. He needed a ride,'' said Detective James Wright of
Metro-Dade police.
   Bartel, 19, of Pembroke Pines, was charged Thursday with auto
theft, his third arrest in a week, Wright said. Bartels was later
released without bond on the auto theft charge as well.
   Bartels was arrested Sept. 2 for burglary to a vehicle when a
car owner found him in his car trying to steal the radio, Wright
said. Detectives searching his pockets found credit cards stolen a
day earlier.
   On Tuesday, Bartels was arrested again for robbery after police
caught him with several womens' purses that had been stolen.
   He was released Wednesday, and stole the van a block away from
court, leading police cars and a helicopter on a 15-minute chase,
Wright said.
</TEXT>
