<FILEID>AP-NR-09-10-88 0613EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Obit-Goodsell     09-10 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Goodsell,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Author Jane Neuberger Goodsell Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jane Neuberger Goodsell, author of
children's biographies of such people as Eleanor Roosevelt, died of
bone cancer in her Portland home. She was 67.
   Mrs. Goodsell, who died Wednesday, also wrote biographies of
Sen. Daniel Inouye, D-Hawaii, and the Mayo brothers, who founded
the Mayo Clinic.
   This year Ballantine Books published her latest children's work,
``Not a Good Word About Anybody,'' a compendium of mishaps and
blunders by historical figures from Cleopatra to Thomas Edison. The
book is in its second printing.
   Mrs. Goodsell's brother was the late Sen. Richard L. Neuberger,
D-Ore.
   Survivors include daughters Ann Goodsell of Cambridge, Mass.,
Kate Marquez of Eugene and Molly Goodsell of Denver; and two
grandchildren.
   Services were scheduled Saturday.
