<NOTE>For Release AMs Monday Sept. 12</NOTE>
<HEAD>AT&T Is Biggest User Of Computers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Telephone & Telegraph Co. heads a list
of 15 U.S. companies that have computer installations worth $200
million or more, Information Week magazine says in its current
issue.
   General Electric Co., GTE Corp., General Motors Corp. and Sears,
Roebuck and Co. round out the top five in the list, which measures
the value of the companies' computers and related communications
equipment.
   For the first time this year the list includes computer
manufacturers and regional telephone companies, although it leaves
out the value of their equipment that is directly connected to
their business specialties, such as the phone companies' switches.
   Here, in order, are the other 10 companies that Information Week
says have installations worth $200 million or more:
   American Express Co., BellSouth Corp., International Business
Machines Corp., Ameritech, Nynex Corp., United Technologies Corp.,
Boeing Co., Dun & Bradstreet Corp., Unisys Corp. and GM's
Electronic Data Systems unit.
   The raw information for the survey is collected by Computer
Intelligence Corp. of Sunnyvale, Calif.
</TEXT>
